Value.value: May the Morninglord light your path
May the Morninglord light your path

value.0: Easily the most wealthy of Djedet's permantent residents, Azizi's stock has increased over the years to include not only potions, but minor magical items. It's unknown where he gets these items, he claims they come from a far away land of demons, drow, and stunningly beautiful women.
A fairly well-to-do merchant, and the town's only female in such a category, Nafrit deals in both local and foreign foodstuffs.

Value.value: I have what you need! Get a bite to eat! Only the best food from all across Faerun!
Idogbe? Who knows what he sells? Point is, he left for Nes'ek!
Soon, I'll have enough money for a slave like Azizi and Unika have. Buy now!

value.0: A man who somehow manages to combine elegance and simplicity, Sabola is said to have been a professional bar fighter, until he found his calling selling fruit and an assortment of metal objects. This odd selection was obviously a good one, as he's made quite a living for himself.

Value.value: Need some pomegranate? I have some! Maybe a knife, or some shears!
I like Qeb. Without him running the show, I think the guards would have made off with more than Jabari has!
Something has always interested me about Kosey. He sells such simple things, but everything he sells seems so useful. Maybe I should go into business with him.

value.0: Known far and wide not only as the richest merchant in Djedet, but also as one of the most successful in all of Mulhorand, Unika uses his slaves to sell his goods while he travels about the kingdom, stopping by in each village to personally see to sales for a few weeks at a time.
A gruff, worn-looking man, this slave must be more intelligent than he appears, as his master, Unika, leaves him to run the shop when the merchant is traveling.

Jabari is known as a willy and cunning thief, or at least pickpocket, at least that's what people suspect. He can't seem to be caught in the act. Fortune didn't always favor him, though, as his lack of a right hand would suggest.

Value.value: Why're you lookin' at me like that? I ain't stealin' nothin'.
Unika's real rich. They say he's one o' the richest merchants in Mulhorand. He travels alot. Leaves all his goods here, too! Er...not that it matters to me.
I'll tell ya. If I were thief, I wouldn't be stealin' from Azizi! Have you seen his slave? Somethin' about him just makes me think he's more than meets the eye.

value.0: Mehsi is a young, quiet girl who makes a living selling semi-precious gemstones and crystals, possibly mined by either her husband or father.

Value.value: Hello to you! I offer only the finest bone and shell jewelry!
My jewelry is the best in Djedet! Better even than Azizi's magical ones!
I hope I can be as successful as Nafrit! She's one of the richest merchants in town!

value.0: A very plain looking man, Kosey sells plain goods. Plain, but still unendingly useful. Perhaps, like his wares, he too is more than meets the eye.
An old woman who always seems to wear both a smile and a glove. Rumor is that she was once wealthy, but has slowly been selling off all her belongings.

Value.value: Hello, dear. Can I interest you in anything?
Donkor is such a tough looking man. I sell the perfect cups to drink his beer!
That Qeb. He was hurt a few years back. He's worn a helmet ever since! Ah, I don't know what we'd do without him.

value.0: A woman known for both her surprisingly good looks, and her uncommon tolerance for hot sand, Nafrini is perhaps most popular because of her well known dexterous hands.

Value.value: Mmm, don't you think Gyasi is so...amazing?
Mesi sells such beautiful jewelry. I really hope she starts to make scarabs.
None of these shops of a scarab brooch. Do you have one?

value.0: A young woman from somewhere near the city of Waterdeep, Flora has been 'just passing through' for almost six months now.

Value.value: Oh, don't mind me. I'm just passing through.
Unika is a legend among merchants! They say he's one of the best in Mulhorand! I bet he has a hard time competing without Azizi!
I don't know what to say about Chin. He scares me. Good he left for Nes'ek.

value.0: A foreign adventurer who seems extremely interested in the wares Kosey sells.

Value.value: Kissa? Wha'? No, I ain't wit' Kissa!
Tha' Thabi'. 'E's a noble, ya know. Wha' I thin', though, is 'at 'e's a wizard.

value.0: Both Nizam's long mustache and his breath have a tendancy to smell rather like tobacco. This isn't an unpleasant smell, though, as it's always mixed with the scent of honey and fruit.
Although softspoken and known for her kindness, Kissa's looks have never made her the most popular. Recently, however, she's been seen spending a lot of time with Unika.

Value.value: Blaera's been here a long time.
Me? With Jama? Oh, um, no.
May the Morninglord light your path
I hate this dust... it dries my lungs, my mouth, my eyes!

value.0:
Taller and stronger than the other guards, Khai takes his job almost as seriously as Adjo. He's been known to be much more relaxed while off duty, but he still manages to detest always being posted with Biti.

He appears to have taken point on helping with repairs.

Value.value: Poor Qeb... may the Eight keep him close...
Welcome to what's left of Djedet. We don't have much left, but we'll keep you safe.
This wasn't how I wanted to be promoted...

value.0: The militia appear to be cleaning up a larger mess and working on building repairs.

You can 'take over' a shop if the sign on it says "closed" or the current shopkeeper isn't in this area. Click one of the signs just outside the door to do so.

Once you have taken over a shop you can use the box named "Yourname's Wares" as a showcase. Place the items you want to sell in it. Every item will be given back to you, and a copy will remain in the box. This copy will be deleted when it's taken out of the box by anyone or when you close your shop.
